Q2.  what is vector?
ANs: In C++, a vector (std::vector) is a dynamic array that can automatically grow or shrink in size when elements are added or removed.

in Array we have below problems :
  fixed size 
  can overfllow and memory waste. 
-->  but that issue not with vector

Benifits: Dynamic size
Automatic memory management
Easy insertion/deletion

